  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenya-Somalia Border Communities Livelihoods Recovery Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(1) Facilitate and support communities, in particular youth and women&#x2019;s groups, to rehabilitate/protect existing water resources and excavate four water pans through cash for work; (2) Facilitate and support communities to develop  water harvesting facilities to schools health centers and any other suitable community facility; (3) Support women and youth groups to rehabilitate key markets and access roads through cash for work; (4) Promote and train subsistence farmers, particularly women and youth, on simple and appropriate technologies  including post harvest management, conservation farming, on farm water harvesting, small scale irrigation and kitchen gardens; (5) Provide seeds for pasture reseeding to 5 groups; (6) Contract 40 farmers for hay production along river Turkwel &amp;amp; Kerio; (7) Facilitate training in business skills development and entrepreneurship, including the establishment of informal savings and loans associations, for women and youth.  Business development will target local and national markets on specific products that are in high demand from refugees and other communities such as dairy products, fresh and dried vegetables, livestock fodder, dried meat, skins and hides, etc.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will target to ease immediate suffering owing to drought and hosting of refugees by creating more strategic and protected water pans.</narrative>
  </description>
